reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These plastic file folders with a clear front pocket have been a game-changer in my organizational routine! The pack of 5 offers a versatile and durable solution for keeping my documents in order. The letter size is perfect for standard papers and ensures a neat and tidy filing system.The clear front pocket is a brilliant addition, allowing me to showcase a cover page or label for quick identification of the folder's contents. This feature is particularly handy when dealing with multiple folders, as it streamlines the retrieval process.The plastic material is sturdy and keeps my documents well-protected. The vibrant colors add a pop of personality to my filing cabinet, making it easy to color-code different categories of documents.I also appreciate the convenience of the pack size – having five folders provides enough flexibility for various projects or subjects. Whether for work or personal use, these folders offer a reliable and visually appealing solution for keeping paperwork organized.If you're in search of practical and durable file folders with an added touch of functionality, this 5-pack is an excellent choice. It combines utility with a thoughtful design for a more efficient and visually pleasing filing system. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A little bit on the flimsy side, but it's getting the job done.
reviews.reviewText: I'm currently using these for various campaigns in a pen/paper game I play. With the label system I can keep track of the various "worlds" and not have to worry about scattered papers here and there getting intermixed.I do like the front insert that comes with the folders, or you can put your own 8.5x11" paper in there to mark each folder.I also like that the top of the folders has a flap that you can move up/down to help tuck the papers into the folder.Additionally, I also liked the "pouches" inside as they stand off from the folder itself to allow you to put your papers in there without them being squished.The only thing that gives me a little pause is that they're not "stiff" like some of the older cardboard type folders we use to roll with back in the day. However, as they are plastic this also means it won't ruin them if someone spills their drink on them. And if you have papers inside the folders that helps to shore up the folder itself. Just bear in mind that there aren't 3 ring holes punched in the folder so you can't put it into a 3-ring binder unless you want to do some punch work yourself.The price is good too, and you'll get five different folders, so I'd recommend picking these up if you need a folder.
